suncertify.db
Class Data

java.lang.Object
  suncertify.db.Data
All Implemented Interfaces:
DBMain
public final class Data
extends java.lang.Object
implements DBMain

Client table access implementation that implements the required DBMain interface. Each client should have its own unique Data instance. The Data instance stores a timestamp for each record that the client has encountered. This lets us detect when a record has been changed by some other client. Each client should only use its own Data instance. This class is thread safe.

find

public int[] find(java.lang.String[] criteria)
Returns an array of record numbers that match the specified criteria. Field n in the database file is described by criteria[n]. A null value in criteria[n] matches any field value. A non-null value in criteria[n] matches any field value that begins with criteria[n]. (For example, "Fred" matches "Fred" or "Freddy".) No lock is required. The records returned will match all the criteria at the time when the request is processed. Note that a record may be modified by another client before "read" is called. The records returned should therefore be treated as a list of possible matches. The caller should call read for each number returned to ensure that it really is a match.

Specified by:
find in interface DBMain
Parameters:
criteria - array of match criteria in the format required by the parser for the corresponding field
Returns:
an array of record numbers of possible matches. An empty array will be returned if there are no matches.

lock

public void lock(int recNo)
          throws RecordNotFoundException
Locks a record so that it can only be updated or deleted by this client. If the specified record is already locked, the current thread gives up the CPU and consumes no CPU cycles until the record is unlocked. If the record is already locked by this client, this method has no effect. Clients may hold multiple locks. Note that the client will automatically lose the lock when the record is deleted.

Specified by:
lock in interface DBMain
Parameters:
recNo - the record number. Must not be negative.
Throws:
RecordNotFoundException - if the record number does not correspond to a record that is not marked as deleted.

unlock

isLocked

Determines if a record is currently locked. Returns true if the record is locked, false otherwise. Note that a record's lock status may be changed by another client thread, so a client should not rely on the value returned by this method.
